M_LOC[ 109] = "There are some ascetics and brahmins who describe the origin of the world in their tradition as having arisen by chance.<br>I go up to them and say,<br>‘Is it really true that this is the venerables’ view?’<br>And they answer, ‘Yes’.<br>I say to them,<br>‘But how do you describe in your tradition that the origin of the world came about by chance?’<br>But they cannot answer, and they even question me in return.<br>So I answer them,";
M_LOC[ 110] = "‘Reverends, there are gods named “non-percipient beings”.";
M_LOC[ 111] = "When perception arises they pass away from that host of gods.";
M_LOC[ 112] = "It’s possible that one of those beings passes away from that host and is reborn in this state of existence.";
M_LOC[ 113] = "Having done so, they go forth from the lay life to homelessness.";
M_LOC[ 114] = "By dint of keen, resolute, committed, and diligent effort, and right focus, they experience an immersion of the heart of such a kind that they recollect the arising of perception, but no further.";
M_LOC[ 115] = "They say,";
M_LOC[ 116] = "“The self and the cosmos arose by chance.";
M_LOC[ 117] = "Long Discourses 25";
M_LOC[ 118] = "The Lion’s Roar at Udumbarikā’s Monastery";
M_LOC[ 119] = "1. On the Wanderer Nigrodha";
M_LOC[ 120] = "Now at that time, Nigrodha was sitting together with a large assembly of wanderers making an uproar, a dreadful racket. They engaged in all kinds of unworthy talk, such as<br>talk about kings, bandits, and ministers; talk about armies, threats, and wars; talk about food, drink, clothes, and beds; talk about garlands and fragrances; talk about family, vehicles, villages, towns, cities, and countries; talk about women and heroes; street talk and well talk; talk about the departed; motley talk; tales of land and sea; and talk about being reborn in this or that state of existence.";
M_LOC[ 121] = "Nigrodha saw Sandhāna coming off in the distance,<br>and hushed his own assembly:<br>“Be quiet, good sirs, don’t make a sound.<br>The householder Sandhāna, a disciple of the ascetic Gotama, is coming.<br>He is included among the white-clothed lay disciples of the ascetic Gotama, who is residing near Rājagaha.<br>Such venerables like the quiet, are educated to be quiet, and praise the quiet.<br>Hopefully if he sees that our assembly is quiet he’ll see fit to approach.”<br>Then those wanderers fell silent.";
M_LOC[ 122] = "Then Sandhāna went up to the wanderer Nigrodha, and exchanged greetings with him.<br>When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to Nigrodha,<br>“The way the wanderers make an uproar as they sit together and talk about all kinds of unworthy topics is one thing.<br>It’s quite different to the way the Buddha frequents remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest that are quiet and still, far from the madding crowd, remote from human settlements, and fit for retreat.”<br>When Sandhāna said this, Nigrodha said to him,<br>“Surely, householder, you should know better! With whom does the ascetic Gotama converse? With whom does he engage in discussion? With whom does he achieve lucidity of wisdom?";
M_LOC[ 123] = "Staying in empty huts has destroyed the ascetic Gotama’s wisdom. Not frequenting assemblies, he is unable to hold a discussion.";
M_LOC[ 124] = "With clairaudience that is purified and superhuman, the Buddha heard this discussion between the householder Sandhāna and the wanderer Nigrodha.";
M_LOC[ 125] = "Then the Buddha descended Vulture’s Peak Mountain and went to the peacocks’ feeding ground on the bank of the Sumāgadhā, where he practiced walking meditation in the open air.";
M_LOC[ 126] = "Then the Buddha went up to the wanderer Nigrodha,";
M_LOC[ 127] = "who said to him,";
M_LOC[ 128] = "“Come, Blessed One! Welcome, Blessed One!";
M_LOC[ 129] = "It’s been a long time since you took the opportunity to come here.";
M_LOC[ 130] = "Please, sir, sit down, this seat is ready.”";
M_LOC[ 131] = "The Buddha sat on the seat spread out,";
M_LOC[ 132] = "Furthermore, a mortifier undertakes a practice of mortification. They glorify themselves and put others down on account of that.";
M_LOC[ 133] = "This too is a defect in that mortifier.";
M_LOC[ 134] = "Furthermore, a mortifier undertakes a practice of mortification. They become indulgent and infatuated and fall into negligence on account of that.";
M_LOC[ 135] = "Furthermore, a mortifier undertakes a practice of mortification. They generate possessions, honor, and popularity through that mortification. They glorify themselves and put others down on account of that.<br>This too is a defect in that mortifier.";
M_LOC[ 136] = "Furthermore, a mortifier undertakes a practice of mortification. They generate possessions, honor, and popularity through that mortification. They become indulgent and infatuated and fall into negligence on account of that.";
M_LOC[ 137] = "This too is a defect in that mortifier.";
M_LOC[ 138] = "Furthermore, a mortifier becomes fussy about food, saying,";
M_LOC[ 139] = "‘This agrees with me, this doesn’t agree with me.’";
M_LOC[ 140] = "Furthermore, a mortifier sees a certain ascetic or brahmin being honored, respected, esteemed, and venerated among good families.";
M_LOC[ 141] = "They think,";
M_LOC[ 142] = "‘This one, who lives in abundance, is honored, respected, esteemed, and venerated among good families.";
M_LOC[ 143] = "But I, a self-mortifier who lives rough, am not honored, respected, esteemed, and venerated among good families.’ Thus they give rise to jealousy and stinginess regarding families.";
M_LOC[ 144] = "This too is a defect in that mortifier.";
M_LOC[ 145] = "Furthermore, a mortifier sits meditation only when people can see them.";
M_LOC[ 146] = "This too is a defect in that mortifier.";
M_LOC[ 147] = "Furthermore, a mortifier sneaks about among families, thinking,";
M_LOC[ 148] = "‘This is part of my mortification; this is part of my mortification.’";
M_LOC[ 149] = "This too is a defect in that mortifier.";
M_LOC[ 150] = "Furthermore, a mortifier sometimes behaves in an underhand manner.";
M_LOC[ 151] = "When asked whether something agrees with them, they say it does, even though it doesn’t.";
M_LOC[ 152] = "Or they say it doesn’t, even though it does.";
M_LOC[ 153] = "Thus they tell a deliberate lie.";
M_LOC[ 154] = "This too is a defect in that mortifier.";
M_LOC[ 155] = "Furthermore, a mortifier disagrees with the way that the Realized One or their disciple teaches Dhamma, even when they make a valid point.";
M_LOC[ 156] = "This too is a defect in that mortifier.";
M_LOC[ 157] = "Furthermore, a mortifier is irritable and hostile …";
M_LOC[ 158] = "Furthermore, a mortifier sees a certain ascetic or brahmin being honored, respected, esteemed, and venerated among good families.";
M_LOC[ 159] = "It never occurs to them,";
M_LOC[ 160] = "‘This one, who lives in abundance, is honored, respected, esteemed, and venerated among good families.";
M_LOC[ 161] = "But I, a self-mortifier who lives rough, am not honored, respected, esteemed, and venerated among good families.’ Thus they don’t give rise to jealousy and stinginess regarding families.";
M_LOC[ 162] = "So they’re pure on that point.";
M_LOC[ 163] = "Furthermore, a mortifier is not irritable and hostile …";
M_LOC[ 164] = "offensive and contemptuous …";
M_LOC[ 165] = "jealous and stingy …";
M_LOC[ 166] = "devious and deceitful …";
M_LOC[ 167] = "obstinate and vain …";
M_LOC[ 168] = "they don’t have wicked desires …";
M_LOC[ 169] = "and wrong view …";
M_LOC[ 170] = "they’re not attached to their own views, holding them tight, and refusing to let go.";
M_LOC[ 171] = "So they’re pure on that point.";
M_LOC[ 172] = "What do you think, Nigrodha?";
M_LOC[ 173] = "If this is so, is the mortification in disgust of sin purified or not?”";
M_LOC[ 174] = "“Clearly, sir, it is purified. It has reached the peak and the pith.”";
M_LOC[ 175] = "“No, Nigrodha, at this point the mortification in disgust of sin has not yet reached the peak and the pith.";
M_LOC[ 176] = "Rather, it has only reached the shoots.”";
M_LOC[ 177] = "2.3. On Reaching the Bark";
M_LOC[ 178] = "“But at what point, sir, does the mortification in disgust of sin reach the peak and the pith?";
M_LOC[ 179] = "Please help me reach the peak and the pith!”";
M_LOC[ 180] = "“Nigrodha, take a mortifier who is restrained in the fourfold restraint.";
